#Approach:

Longest Common Prefix – Sorting Approach

Is problem me hume sabhi strings ka longest common prefix nikalna hota hai.

Is approach me hum pehle poora string array sort kar dete hain.
Sorting ke baad jo first string hogi wo lexicographically smallest hogi
aur last string lexicographically largest hogi.

Longest common prefix sirf first aur last string compare karke mil jayega,
kyunki baaki saari strings unke beech me hongi aur unka prefix bhi same range me hi hoga.

Ab first aur last string ko character by character compare karte hain.
Jab tak characters same hain, tab tak prefix me add karte jaate hain.
Jaise hi mismatch mile, waha stop kar dete hain.

Jo prefix ab tak mila hai wahi longest common prefix hoga.

Time Complexity: O(n log n + m)
n = number of strings
m = length of smallest string
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public String longestCommonPrefix(String[] strs) {
        Arrays.sort(strs);
        StringBuilder result = new StringBuilder();
        int n = strs.length;
        char[] first = strs[0].toCharArray();
        char[] last = strs[n-1].toCharArray();

        int minLen = Math.min(first.length, last.length);

        for(int i=0; i<minLen; i++){
            if(first[i] != last[i]){
                break;
            }
            result.append(first[i]);
        }
        return result.toString();
    }
}
